Source: libmicarray
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: libmicarray Team <maintainer@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13),
               build-essential,
               libasound2-dev,
               libfftw3-dev,
               pkg-config
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://github.com/example/libmicarray
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/example/libmicarray.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/example/libmicarray

Package: libmicarray1
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Multi-microphone array processing library
 libmicarray is a C/C++ library designed for Raspberry Pi to handle
 multiple microphone arrays for stereo localization and noise reduction.
 .
 This package contains the shared library.

Package: libmicarray-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libmicarray1 (= ${binary:Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Development files for libmicarray
 libmicarray is a C/C++ library designed for Raspberry Pi to handle
 multiple microphone arrays for stereo localization and noise reduction.
 .
 This package contains the development files (headers and static library).

Package: libmicarray-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: libmicarray1 (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Command-line tools for libmicarray
 libmicarray is a C/C++ library designed for Raspberry Pi to handle
 multiple microphone arrays for stereo localization and noise reduction.
 .
 This package contains the command-line application for running the
 microphone array processing system.
